<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphex argentifrons" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifrons">Sphex argentifrons</taxonomicName>
F. Smith, 1868: 248, ♀, actually ♂ (see 
<bibRefCitation pageId="63" pageNumber="64">van der Vecht 1973</bibRefCitation>
: 349), junior primary homonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphex argentifrons" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifrons">Sphex argentifrons</taxonomicName>
